Fifty years ago today, on June 17, 1971, President Richard Nixon declared a war on drugs, calling for a "new all-out offensive." Here's the infamous speech that started it all.

The drug war has been an unmitigated disaster and failure on every front. With an unimaginable human, financial and societal cost. Not just in America, where it really began. America exported its drug policies and attitude around the world. 🌎👮‍♂️ 5 decades later, it's still going strong. Yet there are more drugs around than ever before.. 

It's past time to end what Nixon started.
━━━━━━━
Listen to Nixon's words. Think about what came after. When you consider all of the pain, suffering, arrests, human indignity, and lives lost / destroyed as a result of this declaration of "war," it stands among the darkest speeches of all time.

Link in Bio. ⤴️ Keith Villa, Ph.D. - famed brewmaster, beer doctor and inventor of Blue Moon is releasing a book called 'Brewing with Cannabis: Using THC and CBD in Beer.' 🍺🌿 He founded @ceriabrewing in 2018, a start-up brewery which created #Colorado’s first NON-alcoholic, cannabis-infused beer. It was a huge hit!

Now anyone can follow his lead. 📚 Dr. Villa worked w/ #BrewersPublications, a division of @brewersassoc in #Boulder to produce #BrewingWithCannabis.

Available nationwide August 1st: an easy-to-read, science-based guide for brewers at any scale. Offering not only practical instructions / recipes, but a deeper exploration of the plant, cannabinoids & terpenes, and growing / harvesting at home.
━━━━
More of Kieth's story, thoughts & book details at HighTimes.com 🍻
